## Edit 1 — Header: add the Lecture button (after the theme button)

Find the theme button in the header markup:

```html
<button id="shell-theme" class="shell-btn" title="Toggle light / dark theme">☾</button>
```

Insert **immediately after it** (same `.shell-group`):

```html
<button id="shell-lecture" class="shell-btn" title="Lecture display mode — hide the guided inquiry, show the full simulation">🎓 Lecture</button>
```

Do not add it to the transport group on the right; it belongs beside Info/Theme.

## Edit 2 — Runtime: add the `setLectureMode` function

Inside the `Shell = (function(){…})()` IIFE, next to the existing
`function setInquiryCollapsed(on){…}`, add this function (it uses only in-scope
helpers `root`, `inqCards`, `inqShow`, `setInquiryCollapsed`):

```js
function setLectureMode(on){
  root.classList.toggle('lecture-mode', on);
  const b = document.getElementById('shell-lecture');
  if(b) b.classList.toggle('active', on);
  if(on){
    const cards = inqCards();
    if(cards.length) inqShow(cards.length - 1); // jump to last step → onStep(last) paints the complete scene
    setInquiryCollapsed(true);                  // hide inquiry → restore bar
  } else {
    setInquiryCollapsed(false);
    inqShow(0);                                 // re-initiate guided inquiry from step 1
  }
}
```

> **Incremental-onStep fallback (use ONLY if testing shows the jump is incomplete):**
> replace the `if(cards.length) inqShow(cards.length - 1);` line with
> `if(cards.length){ for(let i=0;i<cards.length;i++) onStep(i); inqShow(cards.length-1); }`

## Edit 3 — Runtime: wire the button and re-point the restore bar

In `wire()`, the existing lookups include `const restore = document.getElementById('aside-inquiry-restore');`
and a theme block. Add the Lecture lookup + listener (place it next to the theme
wiring):

```js
const lecture = document.getElementById('shell-lecture');
if(lecture) lecture.addEventListener('click', ()=> setLectureMode(!root.classList.contains('lecture-mode')));
```

Change the existing restore-bar handler so it exits lecture mode (keeping the two
paths consistent — the restore bar re-initiates from step 1 too):

```js
// BEFORE:
if(restore) restore.addEventListener('click',()=>setInquiryCollapsed(false));
// AFTER:
if(restore) restore.addEventListener('click',()=> setLectureMode(false));
```

## Edit 4 — Remove the old Skip button (markup + wiring)

Delete the Skip button **markup** from the inquiry zone head (leave the
`<h3>Guided Inquiry</h3>` and the `.aside-zone-head` wrapper intact):

```html
<button id="aside-inquiry-skip" class="shell-btn aside-skip" title="Skip the guided inquiry">Skip ✕</button>
```

Delete its **wiring** in `wire()` — the lookup line and the listener line:

```js
const skip = document.getElementById('aside-inquiry-skip');   // delete
...
if(skip) skip.addEventListener('click',()=>setInquiryCollapsed(true));   // delete
```

(Leave `setInquiryCollapsed` itself and the restore lookup in place — they are
still used.)

