## Notes / edge cases
- **No-inquiry sims:** if `#inq-cards` has zero `.inq-step` cards (`#shell` gets
  the `no-inquiry` class), the Lecture button has nothing to do — optionally hide
  it, but the last-10 sims all have an inquiry, so normally no action needed.
- **Transport is untouched:** entering/leaving lecture mode must not force
  Play/Pause. Do not add `setPlaying(...)` calls.
- **"Restart at step 1" = show card 1 again** via `inqShow(0)`. This does not wipe
  a student's previous answers by default. If a fully fresh re-run is wanted, that
  is a separate, opt-in enhancement — do not add it unless asked.

## Self-check before finishing
- Loads with **no console errors**; canvas renders; every original slider/readout
  still works; `Next` still gates only on predict cards.
- Header shows `🎓 Lecture` beside the theme button; the old `Skip ✕` is gone.
- Click `🎓 Lecture` → inquiry hides to the `▸ Guided inquiry` restore bar AND the
  scene matches the post-Finish "complete" view (compare against a manual
  click-through + Finish). Button shows its `.active` state.
- Click `🎓 Lecture` again → inquiry re-opens at **step 1**.
- Click the `▸ Guided inquiry` restore bar (while in lecture mode) → also re-opens
  at step 1 and clears the button's active state.
- **Physics/draw code is byte-for-byte unchanged; `simulation-shell.css` untouched.**

